  },
  {
    "heading": "Season",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "unordered_list",
        "content": [
          "Tamil Nadu: September –October (Rainfed) and February –March (Irrigated)",
          "Uttaranchal and North Eastern States: April-May",
          "Dry seeding prior to the onset of monsoon is practiced in hills."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Spacing and Seed rate",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "25 cms between rows and 10 cm between plants within a row"
      },
      {
        "type": "unordered_list",
        "content": [
          "8–10 kg ha -1 for line sowing",
          "12–15 kg ha -1 for broad casting"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Manuring and Fertilization",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "unordered_list",
        "content": [
          "Apply 5 tones of farm yard manure per hectare 2–3 weeks before sowing.",
          "fertilizer required for different states is as follows"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": {
          "rows": [
            [
              "States",
              "Fertilizer recommended NPK kg ha-1"
            ],
            [
              "Andhra Pradesh",
              "20:20:0"
            ],
            [
              "Bihar and Tamil nadu",
              "40:20:0"
            ],
            [
              "Uttar Pradesh",
              "40:20:0"
            ],
            [
              "Other states",
              "20:20:0"
            ]
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Bio fertilizers",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Inoculating seeds with Agrobacterium radiobacter and Aspergillus awamori is recommended"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Weed Control",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "unordered_list",
        "content": [
          "Two inter cultivations and one hand weeding in line sowing",
          "Two hand weeding in broadcasted crop."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Cropping system",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "unordered_list",
        "content": [
          "Barnyard millet + rice bean in 4:1 row ratio is recommended for Uttaranchal"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Diseases",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The crop although affected by three different smuts, the grain smut caused by Ustilago panicifrumentacei is important."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Control : Pre sowing treatment of the seeds with Thiram or Carbendazim @ 2g/kg."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "heading": "Pests",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Shootfly"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "It is the most serious pest causing significant yield losses."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Early sowing with the onset of monsoon is an effective and cheapest method of control."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Source : Indian Institute of Millets Research"
      }
    ]
  }
